      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The myth of meritocracy is a dangerous illusion designed to mask systemic oppression. It falsely implies that success is purely a matter of individual effort, completely ignoring the inherited advantages and disadvantages tied to race and socioeconomic background. In reality, the starting lines are drastically unequal, meaning that \"merit\" is often just a reflection of access to generational wealth and privilege, not inherent talent. Therefore, clinging to this idea serves only to justify the status quo of racial disparity.",
      "source": "target",
